computeIfAbsent

Bash

Copy
hashMap.computeIfAbsent(new Key(1), …)
    → key new Key(1) (val=1, hash=1) is **not** found
      (the only entry with val=1 is k2, which lives in bucket 2)
    → mapping function runs: hashMap.getOrDefault(new Key(2),"X")
        new Key(2) is not present → returns "X"
    → puts (new Key(1),"X") into bucket 1 (bucket now holds k1 then this new entry)

hashMap.computeIfAbsent(new Key(3), …)
    → key new Key(3) (val=3, hash=3) **is** found (k3 lives in bucket 3)
    → mapping function is NOT executed
    → returns the existing value "three"
